        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Midland, or 14 miles southwest of Albemarle. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Badin Lake, Ansonville, Plyler, Locust, Norwood, Badin,
Oakboro, Stanfield, and Morrow Mountain State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
